# Multi-Agent Orchestration

When the user asks to build features, audit, or work on the multi-tenant website, delegate to specialist subagents in `.cursor/agents/`:

| Agent | File | Scope |
|-------|------|-------|
| Front End Developer | `frontend-developer.md` | UI, components, marketing, FMS UX, accessibility |
| Backend Developer | `backend-developer.md` | Prisma, DB, server actions, API, cron, storage |
| Quality Team | `quality-team.md` | P0–P3 gaps, security, regression (readonly) |
| SaaS Multi-Tenant | `saas-multitenant.md` | Provisioning, tiers, enterprise UX patterns |

## Parallel execution

For large tasks (e.g. "make a website", "improve FMS", "multi-tenant work"):

1. Launch **Frontend + Backend in parallel** on non-overlapping files
2. Launch **Quality Team** (readonly) after or in parallel for audit
3. Launch **SaaS Architect** for provisioning/tier/UX architecture

Use `/multitask` or background subagents for parallel workstreams.

## Project context

- Repo: `sheetomatic-redesign` (Next.js 16, Prisma/Postgres, multi-tenant BCI ops platform)
- FMS spec: `.cursor/rules/fms-design-playbook.mdc`, `docs/BCI-FMS-SALES-KIT.md`
- Backlog: `AUDIT_ACTIONS.md`
- Active workstreams: `.cursor/WORKSTREAM.md`

## Coordination rules

- Backend owns `prisma/`, `src/lib/`, server actions
- Frontend owns `src/components/`, page layouts (except action files)
- Quality never edits — reports only
- SaaS architect proposes; Backend/Frontend implement
- Never let two agents edit the same file simultaneously
